1336 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking dish (approx. 30 cm x 20 cm), oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["You can serve the fruit pudding with ice cream, custard or very cold unsweetened yoghurt instead of whipped cream.","Note that the batter recipe always has equal quantities of sugar, butter, eggs and self-raising flour. If you are making a bigger or smaller cobbler, vary the weights we’ve given here depending on the size of the pudding required—always using equal quantities.","You might like the fruit base to be a puree, or a mix of puree and chunks of fruit, or entirely chunky.","Try different types of fruit. For berries, just create a layer of mixed berries in the baking dish and top with batter.","If using apples, pears or quinces, sprinkle the cut fruit with lemon juice to avoid discolouring."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h","4 portions"]}